.TH STRIPCMDS(1),User Commands,STRIPCMDS(1)

.SH NAME
stripcmds - strip control characters from text

.SH SYNOPSIS
stripcmds [-bch]

.SH DESCRIPTION
stripcmds reads standard input and writes it to standard output, dropping bytes that would be interpreted as control codes by the terminal.

By default, only LF (0x0A), CR (0x0D), printable ASCII (0x20..0x7E), extended characters (0xA0..0xFF), and VERBATIM_MODE (0x80) are passed through.
All other bytes - including color-change codes and cursor controls - are removed.

When VERBATIM_MODE (0x80) is emitted, the byte immediately following it is also passed through unconditionally, regardless of the filter in effect.

.SH OPTIONS
-b: Pass all printable bytes through, but still strip color-change control codes (SWAP_COLORS and the COLOR_* codes).
Useful for capturing output that should keep its layout but lose its colors.

-c: Allow color-change control codes to pass through.
The filter still removes other non-printable bytes.

-h: Print a short usage summary and exit 0.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: End of input reached.
